The paper deals with predictive business process monitoring, which involves the use of machine learning and data mining techniques to generate predictions about running instances of a business process. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of historical process execution logs, which suggests that it may be relevant to the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the evaluation of different methods, which suggests that it may be relevant to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the prediction of outcomes and the taking of remedial actions, which suggests that it may be relevant to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
